# 🔹 4. Data Filtering (Pandas)

## ✅ 1. Display all days where Plant_Health_Index > 80

```python
df[df["Plant_Health_Index"] > 80]
```

👉 Matlab: sirf wahi rows dikhao jaha value 80 se zyada hai

---

## ✅ 2. Display records where Rainfall = 0

```python
df[df["Rainfall"] == 0]
```

👉 `==` use hota hai check karne ke liye

---

## ✅ 3. Find the day with highest temperature

```python
df[df["Temperature"] == df["Temperature"].max()]
```

👉 `.max()` → sabse badi value
👉 uske equal wali row nikaal li

---

## ✅ 4. Average Plant Health Index when rainfall > 3

```python
df[df["Rainfall"] > 3]["Plant_Health_Index"].mean()
```

👉 Pehle filter kiya
👉 phir mean nikala

---

# 🔹 5. Aggregation Operations

## ✅ 1. Average soil moisture for each Health_Status

```python
df.groupby("Health_Status")["Soil_Moisture"].mean()
```

👉 group bana → phir average nikala

---

## ✅ 2. Count how many days fall into each Moisture_Level

```python
df["Moisture_Level"].value_counts()
```

👉 count karta hai kitni baar "Low", "Medium", "High"

---

## ✅ 3. Correlation between temperature and plant health

```python
df["Temperature"].corr(df["Plant_Health_Index"])
```

👉 relation check karta hai
👉 +1 → strong relation
👉 0 → no relation

---

# 🔹 6. Data Visualization (Matplotlib)

⚠️ Exam me **code likhna enough hota hai**, graph draw nahi karna hota

---

## ✅ 1. Line Plot (Day vs Plant Health Index)

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

plt.plot(df["Day"], df["Plant_Health_Index"])
plt.xlabel("Day")
plt.ylabel("Plant Health Index")
plt.title("Day vs Plant Health")
plt.show()
```

---

## ✅ 2. Bar Plot (Day vs Soil Moisture)

```python
plt.bar(df["Day"], df["Soil_Moisture"])
plt.xlabel("Day")
plt.ylabel("Soil Moisture")
plt.title("Day vs Soil Moisture")
plt.show()
```

---

## ✅ 3. Scatter Plot (Temperature vs Plant Health)

```python
plt.scatter(df["Temperature"], df["Plant_Health_Index"])
plt.xlabel("Temperature")
plt.ylabel("Plant Health Index")
plt.title("Temp vs Health")
plt.show()
```

